Issue 845 | Have me read it to you | Get the newsletter on time My response=
 to the Oregon Governor=E2=80=99s Prosperity Council Thanks for putting up =
with my constant cajoling on the Oregon Governor=E2=80=99s Prosperity Counc=
il survey. I hope you got the chance to respond. Admittedly, I didn=E2=80=
=99t want to jaundice your response with my response. But now that the subm=
issions have closed I wanted to share what I submitted. Again, my response =
was very myopically focused on the Portland startup community, as is my won=
t. ... More Oregon QSBS tax reform could work =E2=80=94 or it could create =
a $1B hole I complained about the whole QSBS stuff in my own way. And I pro=
vided a very subjective perspective to the Oregon Prosperity Council. But s=
omeone finally did the math on SB 1507, the Oregon bill that disentangles Q=
ualified Small Business Stock tax shelters from the federal tax law and est=
ablishes a 9.9% tax on QSBS returns. And =E2=80=94 shocker =E2=80=94 the nu=
mbers are worse than I thought. ... More All Raise needs your perspective o=
n the current state of VC I know I=E2=80=99ve been asking a lot of you late=
ly. Surveys. Feedback forms. Attending things and stuff. Admittedly, I feel=
 guilty. You=E2=80=99re already overly busy. But sometimes being a founder =
means figuring out how to effectively carve out time to address critical is=
sues. No matter how busy you are. So that=E2=80=99s why I=E2=80=99m shoving=
 that guilt way down and asking you to take this one: All Raise =E2=80=94 l=
ed by Portland=E2=80=99s own Paige Hendrix Buckner =E2=80=94 is running the=
ir annual community survey. ... More When every thing on the Web is AI trai=
ning fodder It=E2=80=99s always super interesting to discuss AI. So many fo=
lks are enamoured of the potential. So many folks are figuring out ways to =
incorporate it into day-to-day activities. And so many folks are super conc=
erned about the every growing number of virtual vacuums that run roughshod =
across the Web, tirelessly scraping the Internet for data to train their mo=
dels. ... More =F0=9F=92=90 Silicon Florist link arrangements Mar 23: AI pr=
oductivity gains, cofounder vetting, AWS cloud empire, and an Oregon compan=
y scandal Mar 24: AI tools, humanoid robots, startup funding trends, and Po=
rtland tech events Mar 25: fjScaler raises $7M, Women.Money. Power. Mar 26:=
 Thoughts on slowing the fuck down Mar 27: Oregon economic challenges, AI d=
evelopments, and community events Photo by Linneas Boland-Godbey
